  {# ============================================================
     WE MUST RISE TOGETHER — stakes
     ============================================================ #}
  <section class="rise-section rise-section--stakes" id="stakes" aria-labelledby="stakes-heading">
    <div class="rise-container rise-section__inner">
      <p class="rise-kicker">We must rise together</p>
      <h2 id="stakes-heading" class="rise-section__title">
        Any other future is either too fragile to last <br class="rise-br-lg"/>or too hollow to want.
      </h2>
      <div class="rise-prose rise-prose--two">
        <p>
          A future where a few ascend and the rest are left behind is not a stable future.
          It fractures. The distances grow. The bonds break.
          What was built on exclusion eventually unmakes itself.
        </p>
        <p>
          A future where everyone is lifted by force, without freedom, without communion —
          that is not a future anyone wants to inhabit.
          A summit no one chose to climb. A paradise that turns out to be a cage.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rise-pullquote">
        <p>The only future worth reaching is the one we reach together.</p>
        <p>The only future that <em>holds</em> is the one we reach together.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {# ============================================================
     THREE CLAIMS
     ============================================================ #}
  <section class="rise-section rise-section--claims" id="claims" aria-labelledby="claims-heading">
    <div class="rise-container rise-section__inner">
      <p class="rise-kicker">Three claims</p>
      <h2 id="claims-heading" class="rise-section__title rise-section__title--sr">Three claims</h2>

      <ol class="rise-claims">
        <li class="rise-claim">
          <p class="rise-claim__numeral">I</p>
          <h3 class="rise-claim__title">Communion must define the future.</h3>
          <p class="rise-claim__body">
            The end we're aiming at is not individual ascension. It's a world in
            which each person's flourishing is bound up with every other's.
            <em>Rising together, not past each other.</em>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="rise-claim">
          <p class="rise-claim__numeral">II</p>
          <h3 class="rise-claim__title">Communion must define the path.</h3>
          <p class="rise-claim__body">
            You cannot reach a communion-shaped future by non-communion means.
            The way we build determines what gets built.
            <em>We become, on the way, what we are trying to arrive at.</em>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="rise-claim">
          <p class="rise-claim__numeral">III</p>
          <h3 class="rise-claim__title">Faith is how communion holds at scale.</h3>
          <p class="rise-claim__body">
            Across generations, under pressure, at civilizational scope — the
            practices that sustain rising-together are not optional decorations.
            They are the infrastructure. Religion at its best, and Christianity
            in particular, is the practice of this posture at real scale.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  {# ============================================================
     WHAT WE ARE ACTUALLY DOING
     ============================================================ #}
  <section class="rise-section rise-section--doing" id="doing" aria-labelledby="doing-heading">
    <div class="rise-container rise-section__inner">
      <p class="rise-kicker">What we are actually doing</p>
      <h2 id="doing-heading" class="rise-section__title">
        Equipping ourselves. Equipping each other.
      </h2>
      <div class="rise-prose">
        <p>Building the tools, the knowledge, the health, the communities, the faith that let us meet whatever comes.</p>
      </div>

      <ul class="rise-doing-list">
        <li>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__label">Own</span>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__body">our data, our learning, our attention.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__label">Open</span>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__body">the door wider than we found it.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__label">Reach back</span>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__body">for whoever is behind us.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__label">Reach forward</span>
          <span class="rise-doing-list__body">for whoever is ahead.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="rise-benediction">
        To be blessed. To bless. <span>To be a blessing.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {# ============================================================
     AUDIENCES
     ============================================================ #}
  <section class="rise-section rise-section--audiences" id="audiences" aria-labelledby="audiences-heading">
    <div class="rise-container rise-section__inner">
      <p class="rise-kicker">An invitation</p>
      <h2 id="audiences-heading" class="rise-section__title rise-section__title--sr">An invitation</h2>

      <div class="rise-audiences">
        <article class="rise-audience">
          <p class="rise-audience__to">To Christians</p>
          <p class="rise-audience__body">
            Christianity has always been a futurism. The kingdom is coming.
            The creation is being renewed. We are called to participate — not
            to retreat. The tools of the age are ours to take up and to
            sanctify. <em>This is what we've been working on.</em>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rise-audience">
          <p class="rise-audience__to">To rationalists and the secular-curious</p>
          <p class="rise-audience__body">
            You were already in the house. You were already loving what we love —
            truth, progress, the flourishing of minds, the refusal to accept
            unnecessary suffering. <em>Come inside where it's warm and you can
            see what you've been touching.</em>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="rise-audience">
          <p class="rise-audience__to">To anyone still reading</p>
          <p class="rise-audience__body">
            We may be wrong. We may fall behind. We may need you to lift us.
          </p>
          <p class="rise-audience__tag">That's the point.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

